Parts of the figure showing the subtype maps and their confluence¶

This figure is going to show the actual subtype maps that show an association with diagnosis and how they represent patterns that are similar.

These are the parts that I want for this figure:

  1. All the protective subtype maps (either individual or as a vertical stack)
  2. All the risk subtype maps (either individual or as a vertical stack)
  3. The ridgeline plot of the protective and risk subtype map patterns
  4. The matrix of subtype map correlation between the risk and protective maps

In Illustrator I will then combine these parts and add the color coding for the risk and protective direction.

def seed_map_overlay(width, height, img, img_idx, over_img, coords, path):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(width, height), constrained_layout=True)
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    gp = nlp.plot_stat_map(nimg.index_img(img, img_idx), cut_coords=coords, axes=ax, colorbar=False)
    gp.add_contours(over_img, filled=False, alpha=1, levels=[0.5], colors='limegreen', linewidths=2)
    fig.savefig(path, bbox_inches='tight', dpi=300, transparent=True, pad_inches=0)
In [12]:
def make_t_table(labels, pheno, weight_str, group, case, control):
    res_list = list()
    for seed_id in range(labels.shape[0]):
        seed_name = labels.iloc[seed_id]['label']
        roi_number = labels.iloc[seed_id]['roi']
        weight = np.load(weight_str.format(roi_number))
        for sbt_id in range(weight.shape[1]):
            results = asdfc.stats.t_test(weight[:, sbt_id], pheno, group, case, control)
            results['seed_id'] = roi_number
            results['seed'] = seed_name
            results['subtype'] = sbt_id+1
            results['subtype_name'] = f'{seed_name}_{sbt_id+1}'
            res_list.append(results)
    table = pd.DataFrame(data=res_list)
    # Add FDR correction
    table.loc[:, ('FDR')] = smi.multipletests(table.p, alpha=0.05, method='fdr_bh')[0]
    table.loc[:, ('q_value')] = smi.multipletests(table.p, alpha=0.01, method='fdr_bh')[1]
    # Add confidence intervals for the correlation (effect size estimates)
    N = weight.shape[0]
    #table.loc[:, ('ci')] = [ci_corr(row['cohens_d'], N) for rid, row in table.iterrows()]
    return table

# Give me the sorted negative effects (CON > ASD)
sbt_neg_idx = sbt_idx[eff<0]

sbt_pos_idx = sbt_idx[eff>0]

# Sort the seed regions by the average within seed overconnectivity of the protective subtypes 
# from high to low
roi_sort = np.argsort(roi_mean)[::-1]

f = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 8))
gs = gridspec.GridSpec(nrows=18, ncols=1, hspace=-0.5)
for fig_idx, roi_id in enumerate(roi_sort):
    roi = labels.iloc[roi_id]['roi']
    roi_mask = atlas_vec==roi
    neg_roi_vec = sbt_arr[sbt_neg_idx, :][:, roi_mask]
    prot_roi_vec = prot_sbt_avg[roi_mask]
    pos_roi_vec = sbt_arr[sbt_pos_idx, :][:, roi_mask]
    risk_roi_vec = risk_sbt_avg[roi_mask]

    pos_ind_color = 'lightblue'
    neg_ind_color = sbn.xkcd_rgb['light pink']
    
    ax = f.add_subplot(gs[fig_idx])
    sbn.distplot(prot_roi_vec, ax=ax, color='navy', hist=False)
    sbn.distplot(risk_roi_vec, ax=ax, color='tomato', hist=False)

    l_prot = ax.lines[0]
    l_risk = ax.lines[1]

    x_prot = l_prot.get_xydata()[:,0]
    y_prot = l_prot.get_xydata()[:,1]
    x_risk = l_risk.get_xydata()[:,0]
    y_risk = l_risk.get_xydata()[:,1]
    ax.fill_between(x_prot,y_prot, color="darkgreen", alpha=0.5)
    ax.hlines(0, -0.2, 0.2)
    ax.fill_between(x_risk,y_risk, color="tomato", alpha=0.5)
    (y_min, y_max) = ax.get_ylim()
    ax.vlines(0, y_min, y_max, zorder=0)
    # Individual protective maps
    #sbn.distplot(neg_roi_vec[0, :], ax=ax, color=pos_ind_color, hist=False, norm_hist=True)
    #sbn.distplot(neg_roi_vec[1, :], ax=ax, color=pos_ind_color, hist=False, norm_hist=True)

    #sbn.distplot(neg_roi_vec[3, :], ax=ax, color=pos_ind_color, hist=False, norm_hist=True)
    #sbn.distplot(neg_roi_vec[4, :], ax=ax, color=pos_ind_color, hist=False, norm_hist=True)

    # Individual risk maps
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[0, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[1, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[2, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[3, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[4, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)
    #sbn.distplot(pos_roi_vec[5, :], ax=ax, color=neg_ind_color, hist=False)

    ax.set_xlim([-0.2, 0.2])
    ax.patch.set_facecolor('None')
    if fig_idx==17:
        ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
        ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
        ax.spines['left'].set_visible(False)
        ax.spines['bottom'].set_visible(True)

        ax.set_xticklabels(['-0.2\nBelow Average Connectivity', -0.1, 0, 0.1, '0.2\nAbove Average Connectivity']);
    else:
        ax.set_axis_off()
    #ax.set_title(labels.iloc[roi_id]['name'])
    ax.text(-0.21, y_max*0.2, labels.iloc[roi_id]['label'], ha='right', va='center')

fc_list = list()
group_list = list()
network_list = list()

for rid, row in sorted_dx_table.iterrows():
    roi = row['seed']
    roi_id = row['seed_id']
    sbt_id = row['subtype']
    idx = row.index
    roi_mask = atlas_vec==roi_id
    sbt_within = sbt_arr[rid, roi_mask]
    n_voxel = len(sbt_within)
    fc_list += list(sbt_within)
    network_list += [roi]*n_voxel
    
    if row.cohens_d < 0:
        # Protective
        group_list += ['protective'] * n_voxel
    else:
        # Risk
        group_list += ['risk'] * n_voxel
        
table = pd.DataFrame({'FC':fc_list, 'effect':group_list, 'network':network_list})
